==English==

===Etymology===
1751, from earlier term {{term|colloquy}} (a conversation), from {{L.}} {{term|colloquium|lang=la}} (conference, conversation), from {{term|con-|lang=la}} (together) + {{term|loqui|lang=la}} (speak). 

===Adjective===
'''colloquial'''

# {{linguistics}} Denoting a manner of speaking or writing that is characteristic of [[familiar]] conversation; [[informal]].
# Of or pertaining to a [[conversation]]; [[conversational]] or [[chatty]].

